Jun 8 2009 	For Twenty Somethings	Got a great deal off a website to stay here before Thanksgiving for $50 a night, which was worth what I got. Rooms are good, clean, with a large bathroom, and view of neighboring tower and of the strip. Casino area is fairly lame, and houses a cineplex and some food courts so it had a very mall-ish feel to it. Mostly very young clientele (which they are targeting with tattoo parlor on premises) so I think really 19-21 yr old college kids would like this as a first time Vegas experience, not really for anyone else. It's too far to walk to the strip or old vegas so you have to cab it. And past midnight there seemed to be lots of single ladies playing the slots, directly in the path to the room elevators. Take that to mean what you will, just an observation. Overall good value, but more a first time Vegas place for kids on a roadtrip (with a vehicle).	
