May 23 2009 	Great Place but Too Much Cig Smell in the Air"	I stayed at the Palms from Tuesday through Friday. The service was outstanding, very friendly people everywhere you go.I booked the room through my airline and got a bargain basement rate of $59.00 per night. For some reason, when I checked in, my room was upgraded. The room had a king sized bed and was huge. Everything was super clean. During the day, as soon as you walk into the front foyer of the casino, the smoke smell hits you. It’s terrible. Strange, though, the air in the evening is much easier to tolerate. Maybe they don’t run the same type of ventilation during the day. For that reason, I won’t stay there again. Casino air quality has improved in the last few years, so I’ll go to those places. As soon as Friday came around, the medium age of the clientle changed. Crazy party hardy 20 somethings infested the casino. For me, it’s not fun to see a bunch of drunk college kids on the prowl like Spring break. Been there. Done that.The spa is absolutely, totally amazing. Lori (from Hawaii) did my facial (enzyme something) and my skin is wonderful. Worth the time and money. Allow extra time to take advantage of everything the spa has to offer during your service (steam room, hot tub, etc…)It's really OK being away from the strip if you have a car or don't mind the cab fare. While you're there, you can get a tatoo. Great tasting salsa and drinks at the Mexican restaurant in the lobby area. Nice food court, too, if you're hungry and need a quick something.	
May 20 2009 	Not bad at all but not great either.	I've stayed at 18 hotels in Vegas, and this hotel is average. It's a good walk to the strip.With the only Playboy Club still in existence, and with Playboy Bunny pictures on every column in the casino, you would think that this hotel would be sexier than most, but it's not. The cocktail waitress outfits are not revealing like at the Rio.The pool has a contemporary (snobbish) design, and is not all that attractive. Same with the interior design of the buffet.The buffet is a great deal, however, unlike most hotels on the strip.The room was nothing special, although I liked the bathroom.The spa is fantastic, and I got free passes while I was there, which is very rare for strip hotels.The Playboy Club is just a place to sit around and drink, with $25/hand blackjack-dealer bunnies. I got a free pass with my stay here.I enjoyed my stay here, and periodically go back for the buffet, and with the TV show &quot;The Real World&quot; filmed here, and the Playboy Club here, you expect more, but the Hard Rock Hotel and Planet Hollywood are more cutting edge for the young folk. But you can't go wrong staying here.	
