Oct 25 2008 	We finally got to stay at the Palms!	After several years of playing annually at the Palms casino we finally got an invitation for 2 comped nights at the Palms hotel.My wife and I are not what you would call high rollers; we each play mostly $1 slots, averaging 8 hours per day. The comp offers we've been receiving from the Palms (and several other casino-hotels) were a nice surprise. We were able to book a total of 8 comped nights.I figured Vegas must be really hurting to have to chase the likes of us. From our rooms overlooking the strip we could see several construction projects that appeared dormant for the entire week we were there. I would expect a visitor could find some good room deals.The room, which was in the older tower, was very nice and appeared to have been recently refurbished. My wife was not happy that the bathroom vanity did not provide enough surface space for all of her &quot;stuff&quot;, but she agreed the bed was very comfortable.The Palms is located almost a mile west of the strip on Flamingo, but we did not mind the walk to Caesar's and several nearby (by Vegas standards) strip properties in the pleasant September weather. If you only want to walk a few blocks, free shuttles from the Rio run constantly to other Harrah's properties. The Palms casino is outstanding, and has been a favorite with locals for years. It is probably the best place in town to see celebrities. There is an excellent mix of decent payback machines and table games, and non-smokers will appreciate the excellent ventilation. The Palms seems to be &quot;the place&quot; for &quot;the beautiful people&quot;, and although we are not such people, they are fun to watch. Several times while we were there we saw a bunch of hot young girls being followed by a 5 man camera. We were told they were filming a TV show called &quot;Nasty Girls&quot; or &quot;Mean Girls&quot; or something like that for a cable channel we don't watch. Our favorite part of the Palms was the buffet. We ate most of our meals there almost for free (our MVP player cards gave us a huge discount). The changing choices and quality was the best we have ever seen on a buffet, and we know our buffets. Many buffets offer a better selection, but lower quality food. The buffet staff was very friendly and helpful.Now if we can just score some comps for December...	
