Sep 4 2008 	Disappointed	My husband and I decided to stay at the Palms for Labor Day weekend because one of his friends recommended it. Throughout our stay at the Palms we had nothing but problems. When we first checked in the lady at the front desk was pretty rude. She made it seem like we were wasting her time. Once we got to our room we basically spent half the evening calling the front desk to have our jucuzzi tub cleaned out. Our jucuzzi may have looked clean, but once we turned on the jets a lot of black fuzzy stuff started to come out. After about 20 to 25 min. a lady came up to clean out the jucuzzi. To try to clean out the black fuzz she poured some chemicals (using more than what she was suppose to, my husband and I found it hard to breath from all the fumes) and let it sit for about 5 min. After 5 min. have past she told us that should of cleaned out the black fuzz. Once the lady left we filled the jucuzzi tub up, and again once we turned on the jets black fuzz still started to come out. Again we had to call front desk to have someone come up. The same lady that cleaned the tub the first time came back, and instead of pouring more chemicals she this time pops out the jets to see what the problem is. Turns out there was a bunch of build up inside the jets. My husband and I were creeped out when we saw how much build up there was. Anyways, she finally fixed the problem by cleaning out all the jets. Besides the jucuzzi tub we were also having problems with the air. We would blast the air on high but if you sat next the window that was the only place you would feel the cool air. Everywhere else in the room you wouldn't feel the air. When it came time to check out we noticed on our summary bill that they charged us for the mini bar. Eventually after a couple times of calling the front desk they had the mini bar charge taken off our bill. After this experience I will not be going back to the Palms. This place is perfect for people who just want to party, but if