r bill was yet another $1/day &quot;Line Access Fee&quot; for the phone in our room, even though we never used it once. When I asked the front desk person about the $1 charge, she shrugged and said &quot;yeah, I know that is the dumbest thing you've probably ever seen but the hotel manager wants it there so there is nothing I can do about it&quot;. So, it seems that the management is the true cause of the hotel being 100% crap and pulling ridiculous $1 scams.The food was okay, the casino is very small. Overall, this was a terrible experience and I highly... HIGHLY... recommend anyone young and looking for fun in Vegas to stay at the Hard Rock or Planet Hollywood since both have excellent clubs and much (MUCH) better management and service.	
