e issues. No one ever did. I find it very hard to believe from 11am until 5pm, no one was available. I left both my and my husband's cell phone numbers.At this point, we were just done. Again, we were offered to for the third time switch rooms to yet a even smaller room, which is not what we paid for. So we checked out right then and there. The front desk agent listened to what I had told her and our nightmare of a stay. She said she would discuss it with the manager ( once she found him) and try to credit us back for our 2 nights. Now, at NO point was I ever told, we could have checked out early. I was told we could not. Had I know this, we would have left the night before. She promised me someone from management would call me. This was June 2nd. It is now June 4th and no one ever called.Erin, we travel to Vegas every 3-5 weeks and were really looking forward to a stay at the Palms. From the very minute we checked in, to the unexpected check out we were not only disappointed, but shocked at the lack of customer service. I still have no idea what happened to the money we paid for our &quot;upgrade&quot;, or better yet, why no one ever bothered to call us from management in the past 2 days? Is customer service that unimportant? I expect a FULL refund of the 2 nights we paid for in advance. I am also forwarding this letter to American Express, the Arizona Attorney General and Trip Res.com. I would hate to see any other customers be treated this poorly. Please feel free to contact me anytime at***********Sincerely-Kim Puente	
Jun 3 2008 	Great atmoshere and value for money at the Palms	My boyfriend and I stayed at the Palms in March 2008 for 4 nights on our 1st trip to Vegas (hopefully the 1st of many). It was a very last minute thing, and I was looking forward to it more than him, however, his opinion quickly changed ! I might just mention now that we like to be surrounded by luxury and comfort and this, along with a great atmosphere and central location often influences our choice of hotel ! Before leaving Ireland we noticfied the hotel of our late arrival (10pm). We actually arrived at 11pm, due to the fact that we had to pick up our rental car at the airport and this took longer than we expected. The hotel is approx 10-15 mins drive from airport. (and depending on the room you get you can see planes landing and taking off!) Even though we arrived so late, we were greeted kindly by the valet assistant and the bellboy and escorted straight to check in. There were no ques which was great b/c we were ready for bed after a long flight! The girl at check-in was lovely, very helpful and in good form and acknowleged that we were Irish and that it was St Patricks Day. We were pleasantly surprised when she informed us about the different hotels and spots which were celebrating the holiday ! She provided us with complimentry passes to all the clubs and recommended the NINE restaraunt for food. (I would not recommend it - I'll tell you why later!)We asked for a room with a strip view on a high floor and we weren't dissapointed ! We stayed on the 27th floor in the Palms tower. Although the rooms were pretty basic, its what we expected for what we paid(€260 for 4 nights-reasonable enough).The rooms were large and the bathroom was fairly sizeable too! I was delighted to find Aveda shower goodies and these were topped up daily !We hit the hay but woke up early the next morn! We ate breakfast at the buffet ( $17 for 2 people) which is in the main lobby area each day and I have to say it was surprisingly good value for money, I'm a picky eater and I had plenty to choose from, my boyf was in breakfast heaven when he saw the selection! After a day of sightseeing on the Strip we returned to find our room had been cleaned thouroughly. This was the case each day of our stay and we left a nice tip for the cleaning lady. We skipped dinner that night as we had a huge late lunch and we headed to Ghostbar. We loved it there !!! The atmoshere was electric and to top it all off the VIEW was amazing ! A must for anyone visiting Vegas for the 1st time ! We met two guys form New York who were lovely and we had great craic with them!**So, overall, so far so good !! Then....the only lowlight of the trip -NINE......Based on the reviews we read, my boyf made a reservation early one morning for NINE steakhouse for that night through the concierge, the guy was lovely and assured us that the reservation was made. We headed off to the Grand Canyon for a day trip, we barley ate all day as the food was mediocre and overpriced so you can imagine we were famished when we returned to the Palms at 7pm. Our dinner reservation was for 8pm, so we quickly showered and changed into our finery and made our way to the restaraunt. Upon entering, it is worth noting how apparent it is that you are in the company of wealthy guests and fellow diners (excuse me for being so blatent about it but thats just how it was) Really looking forward to our meal only to be told by a ditzy young lady who was no more interested in her job than the man on the moon, that we had NO RESERVATION under our name and that there were no tables available. After insisting that we had very much so made a reservation that morning, she proceeded to insult us even further by suggesting we were at the wrong restaraunt !! I'm sure I was showing how agitated I was at this stage so after calling all the other restaraunts in the hotel (and confirming that we were not eating in any of them), she told us to take a seat at the bar and wait to be accomodated on such short notice (Ehhh WE HAD A RESERVATION!!). So we waited ! We were served at the bar by a really lovely guy (who happened to be from Ireland but was living in Vegas for the last 20 years). He gave us complimentary drinks and offered us bar food appetisers while we waited but we declined. 35 minutes later and THREE trips to ask where our table was we were rudely told by miss ignorant to wait our turn while we watched high rollers be attended to immedialtley (and probably with no reservation too !!). This was soo not the service we were expecting so we left NINE to dine elsewhere. It kind of ruined our evening and for this reason I would recommend you stay away, or get your reservation in writing !!!On our last night we hit Ghostbar again, and had a really good time again, we decided to leave and check out the Playboy Club but got side-tracked and ended up in Moon in the Fantasy Tower !! Savage nightclub although I think it may be a little over-hyped but none the less we still had a fantastic night with breath-taking views of the Strip agian ! A far stretch from any night club iin Dublin!!On Friday after some more shopping and sightseeing on the Strip we decided to check out the pool and being Ditch Friday the place was really lively ! Great music, great weather and great drinks, one of the many hightlights of the trip, however we were checking out that afternoon so couldn't stay long but it was the perfect way to end a fantastic trip to Vegas !!Overall, I would return, great value for money, not on the Srtip but close enough to all the action for us!! Steer clear of NINE and you'll be fine !!!	
