hrough 7:00 pm, but since you have 15 girls we can maybe get you on the list at one of our clubs.” The rooms were ready soon after but I felt like saying, “thanks [profanity], but we already have a table at Tryst tonight which absolutely blows away any of the Palms clubs---all I want is my [profanity] room.” Thirdly, the rooms look like they haven’t been updated in years. Best description I can give is old office furniture and lighting that is non-existent in the bathroom. The space was large and the comforters were nice, but that is the extent of the positives in this place. In short, don’t ever stay here but if you do get standard rooms.Fourthly, the casino is nothing special and the restaurant selection and staff combined equals a bad idea. Stay away from 24/7 (food is bland and they don’t want to serve you water---I will explain the water situation later). Lastly, and most importantly, this place must have a water ban. I don’t get it. They pretty much refuse to serve you water at the pool or anywhere else even though you are still tipping for it. I pretty much drank heavily both nights and drank during the day Saturday and sometimes a girl just needs a glass of water to prevent having a heart attack. I even ordered water at McDonald’s and they were out---I mean they ran out of bottled water and they didn’t have regular water and it’s a McDonald’s---unbelievable!!! The best part about it all is that they force you to throw away any drinks before you go into the pool. So even though we had just bought bottled water in their gift shop directly outside the pool, it had to go directly in the trash only for them to not serve us when we got in there. Oh, and the last day the door woman went through my friend’s purse and she had a 100 calorie pack in it from the plane and the woman goes, “NO SNACKS AT THE PALMS.” Not only is this ridiculous, but to use the word “snack” over “food or drink” is honestly just comical. Shows the level of intelligence you have to have to work here.Bottom line, everyone “working” at the Palms is looking for a handout. They want to get tipped big, but they don’t want to work. And sadly Palms staff, that isn’t how the world works---not even in Vegas. We were really excited because it’s so hyped up, but honestly that’s all this place is. If I were Maloof I would slowly fire, retrain and rehire every staff member working here from top to bottom. With the economy in recession, there is no way a hotel like this will continue to do well amongst such phenomenal competition.My fiancé and crew stayed at the Venetian and the rooms were phenomenal, the casino was beautiful and Tao Beach was amazing. If you are looking for a fun pool (which is really the Palms' only attraction), definitely check out Venetian.	
