May 11 2008 	Past it's prime	We stayed at the Palms for three nights at the beginning of May 2008. There were several reasons why we decided on the hotel...1) The group we were traveling with had already booked their rooms 2) The nightlife 3) The pool. CHECK IN: Check in was painless. We were fortunate to meet DJ at the front desk who was extremely friendly and informative. He provided us with passes to the nightclubs and even upgraded our room to the Fantasy Tower superior. Our flight arrived early and we were checked in by 1 PM.ROOM: The superior room in the fantasy tower was nice. LCD TV, nice bathroom with jacuzzi tub, and two double beds. One of the beds was actually broken and in horrible shape. After going back down to the front desk and advising the staff of the problem , the bed was replaced within a few hours. It was extremely comfortable and wasn't a big deal. They gave us the option to change rooms, but it wasn't worth it after already unpacking.POOL: The pool area at the Palms is nice. We went everyday and the best day was definately Friday (Ditch Friday). Packed with people, yet alot of fun. Service was mediocre at best and I found some of the bartenders so overwhelmed that they were nasty to some of the people waiting. If you don't go on Friday, there are less people. CASINO: Very small with not enough tables. We gambled at the other casinos more than the Palms. Mediocre dealers at the Palms and absolutely no excitement here.RESTAURANTS: We had dinner at Nove Italiano and it was excellent from the food to the service. Worth the money. We also dined at the restaurant &quot;24/7&quot; and it easily had the worst service I've received at a restaurant in five (yes 5) years. SLOW, SLOWER, SLOWEST. Every customer in there was obviously upset and I can't see how they survive on tips. There is also a food court at the Palms with your average fast food and a coffee shop serving three dollar coffee (per cup). Not even Starbucks. NIGHTCLUBS: I think many people travel to the Palms for the nightlife. Well, look elsewhere, the Palms has been left behind by all the clubs on the strip. Ghostbar was cool with a view , but the guy to girl ratio is 65/35 and the drinks were about 10 a pop. Wouldn't care about the price, but the place just has a view now. Not that fun. We also witnessed a girl's purse and camera get jacked from her table when she got up for a few minutes. Security came and tried to rectify the situation. They found out who took the items but DID NOT throw the dude out. Come on. As for Moon. Again, nice view and same price on drinks. At least here you get a dance floor and a retractable roof. Other than that, pretty lame. Playboy Club was cool if you like a lounge type place. It's really nice but more like a place to gamble, smoke cigars and sip scotch while you take in the atmosphere. Last but not least Rain. I remember Rain three years ago when it was one of the best clubs in Vegas. Now? Easily one of the worst. Guy/Girl ratio was 80/20 (scary). Thankfully we had comp admission and did not have to wait on the line b/c the place....sucked. The Palms can no longer compete with the newer clubs/bars elsewhere in Vegas. CHECK OUT Just a few notes here. Our flight was departing very late so I asked if we could check out three hours past normal time, understanding that they couldn't let us stay too long. I figured a nominal fee but got a quote of $250.00 for the extra three (yes 3) hours. I also noticed some extra charges on our room bill for things from the in room bar that we never took. They were removed.SUMMARY The Palms is your average off the strip hotel. It's all hype that they have been living off of since 2004. If you go, stop by for DItch Fridays at the pool or have dinner at Nove Italiano. Stay away from the clubs unless you like to party with all men. There are so many other places to go in Vegas and the hotel is not convenient nor is it what it used to be. Horrible hotel? No. Mediocre with few bright spots, yes. I don't intend on returning.	
