Apr 25 2008 	Business trip at the Palms	Stayed for 5 nights in April 2008 for a business trip. Check in and out was very smooth. Room very spacious, clean and comfortable. Lots of security. No balcony but good view of the mountains. Excellent toiletries including toothpaste, deodorant, etc. Food was very expensive - $2.50 for a soda in the mini bar and meals at the restaurants in the $40+ range. This hotel is for the elite young partying crowd, not for average people on vacation. There was constant loud contemporary music playing everywhere. People were very dressed up (like in a fashion magazine) all times of the day. It is a mile from the strip so you have to take a taxi for $11 each way (no sidewalks to walk to it). Pool area is small....I did not use it but others complained that there was no place to lounge. The casino is not very spacious and full of smokers...both cigarettes and cigars. There was no escape from the smoke as the reception area and several restaurants are a few feet from the border of the casino. The hotel has free valet parking which was very efficient. Every employee that I came in contact with was very professional and friendly. Although the accomodations were fine, I would not stay here again due to the location and atmosphere.	
