Apr 7 2008 	Great Time at The Palms	After reading some of the reviews on this site I was a little skeptical about staying at The Palms, especially since my husband and I love the Hard Rock. Now after our stay in the middle of March, this is now my favorite hotel in Las Vegas. Everyone we came in contact with in hotel, from the front desk, player's club membership, dealers and the waiter at Nove all went out of their way to make our stay a positive one. Everyone was extremely nice and helpful. The casino is a perfect size, you don't get lost going to the bathroom. Plenty of open tables and slot machines. The room was in the original tower and was very nice with a decent view. We got free passes to Ghostbar, Moon and the Playboy club. We saw Matchbox Twenty at The Pearl and enjoyed every minute of it. This is a great venue for concerts. We are in our early 40's and did not feel out of place at all in this hotel and will recommend it.	
