Mar 13 2008 	Pretty Good	Booked junior suite for 6 nights in December on a deal from tripres.com for $72 a night. For the price, def worth it. However, if I was paying retail of around $200 a night, I'd look for something on the strip, since there's not much to walk to around the hotel, and the strip is around a 20-25 minute walk. Room was in the old tower but pretty nice, lot of room and new, very comfortable bedding. Didn't go to Vegas for the rooms anyway. Casino was nice but much smaller than other hotels. If one was looking for a more intimate casino experience then the Palms would be good. We went to Moon one night since my friend was betting $100-$1000 hands, so everything was compted and we got a VIP room. Clubbing isn't really my thing (I'm married) but the view was amazing and the $1000 bottle of Blue Label was pretty good (comped, thank G-d). My friend's ID and credit card were actually stolen from the club, but the casino caught the guy the next day so he got it back. All in all had a good time, but I think next time I'd def pick something mid-strip.	
