Dec 22 2007	Palms was ok	The Palms hotel is located off the strip FYI. Not far at all but you will need to catch a cab or rent a car to make it there. I stayed for 5 nights on business in a Jr Suite in the original tower. The bed was decent, they had Aveda toiletries, free shick shaver for men, rhoto eye drops, and toothpaste. Wifi internet in the room was $12.99 per 24hrs.Elevators were fast and always working. In the evening you need to show your room card to the security guard at the elevator bank.Little Buddha restaurant was good! nice atmosphere, good food, decent cocktails. But I prefer Tao Asian restaurant in the Venetian hotel over Little Buddha any day. Much better food, drinks, and ambiance. I highly recommend it.The 24hr cafe downstairs at the Palm is great for breakfast (much better than the buffett on the casino floor). The workout gym is good but costs $45 for a 3 day pass or $20 per day. Mens lockerroom has the steam room, dry sauna, cold and hot plunge pools, outdoor hot tub, showers, and lounge room with fresh fruit and snacks while you watch tv. Assorted drinks are provided as well. The gym is open 6am to 8pm. Free weights and nice cardio machines with TV are all available.Parking is free at the Palms and they have a small food court with popular chains and a large theater complex.If i were going back, I would stay at THEhotel at Mandalay Bay	
