Dec 12 2007	It's sure not like old vegas...	Stayed here for our annual Thanksgiving Vegas trip. $59 for a Fantasy Tower room is a good value but, once outside of the room, the Palms' appeal falls off fast. I know the Maloofs are trying for a younger, hipper slice of Vegas with this joint, but they've completely chucked all the hallowed conventions of the Vegas experience. The nightclubs rule this place, followed by the concerts, with the gambling a distant third. The casino is a ghost town almost all of the time, and the poker room doesn't even offer tourneys. The room was great, with a very comfy bed and outstanding soundproofing. I tried the buffet only for breakfast - the food was good and the price was right ($7.99), but it didn't open until 8AM! This is a good place to sleep, but go elsewhere for a real Vegas experience.	
