 were over flowing in the gym, with empty water bottles. In the men's lockerroom, fruit basket had one apple. Asked for a banana, and was told sure thing. Came out of my shower, same apple left, trash cans not emptied. Said, could I get that banana? Oh, right, sure thing, they finally arrived. Rude waitress at the 24-Cafe. Sink still backed up. And to top it off, day of check-out, we called down to the front desk for a late check-out at 1pm, and at 1130am, they sent a family of 4 with 2 babies to our room to occupy it. I felt so bad for them. The hotel comped us our last night, and took off the internet charges, for about a $150 savings. The concierge was helpful and got us Celine tickets for the same day on Friday. Other than that, and the fact that, yes, it is a nice chic LOOKING hotel, their operations need a serious overhaul. I wouldn't recommend the Palms.	
Jul 10 2007 	Modern young and fun	My husband and I stayed at the Palms from Sunday through Tuesday in early July. Check-in was seamless, and we were upgraded from a deluxe guestroom to a junior suite. We were disappointed at first, as we were hoping for a superior guestroom in the newer Fantasy Tower, but our room was generously-sized (especially the bathroom--loved the Aveda amenities, plus toothpaste, women's razor and eyedrops) and featured two windows with fantastic views (one faced the mountains and the other faced the strip. I had read previously about the indifference of hotel/casino staff, but the staff I encountered during my stay were nothing but courteous and professional. The only customer service grievance I have is that I had left my mobile phone charger plugged in when I checked out of the room, and no one was able to return it to me (even after a visit to the front desk and multiple phone calls over the next two days). We visited the pool late Sunday afternoon, and were able to find a comfortable wicker chair for two. The pool definitely has a party atmosphere best suited to twentysomethings, but we saw a couple children who appeared to be having fun. We were unable to attend the nightclubs (we were given free passes and line passes at check-in) and restaurants due to time constraints, but did order room service. Delivery was fast and friendly. The food court offered a wide variety of fast food options, from McDonalds to Chinese to Pizza to Ben &amp; Jerrys. As for the casino itself, I noticed a mix of older patrons who may have been locals, along with the younger clientele. The decor is modern, yet classy--a departure from the traditional Vegas flash. A side note: I read somewhere that there's nothing for kids to do at the Palms, however, I noticed a storefront for a children's program just inside the food court. Overall, my husband and I both enjoyed the Palms and would love to return.	
