Apr 9 2007 	A Few things to know before you go!	My wife and I just got back from spending six nights at the Palms. I wanted to touch on a few things that I wish I had known before I left. We had a very early flight out of Philadelphia, I wanted to get to Las Vegas in plenty of time to enjoy my first day of vacation, when the Palms says check in is a three- they mean it! I knew that getting there at 10:30 am would be too early to check in, the front desk took my number and said they would call as soon a room was ready. We found plenty to do until 2:30 when I checked back at the desk where the female employee let me know that &quot;check in is 3 not 2:30&quot; after a six hour flight I really just wanted to check in a get a shower. Once we did get to our room it was great. We stayed in the fantasy tower which had a huge king size bed a hot tub and great views! I spent some time at the sportsbook which has very nice employees....keep in mind that you can't bet on NBA action as the owners of the Palms also own an NBA team. For food I would hit the cheaper spots like 24/7 and stay away from the high end places. We spent over $200 on a meal for two at Nove and the food was not that great. I would plan on hitting the pool, get there early as it gets busy by noon. The staff there is outstanding! If you plan on getting food or drink keep in mind that it is going to take A LONG TIME until you see your server again with your drink of food....if your really in a rush just hit the bar that is right by the pool. We did go to the Pearl to see a UFC event this venue is top notch. I am sure any event held there would be worth going to see. The Palms was a very nice hotel just dont plan on getting to your room anytime before three!!!	
