sk which at that point were not helpful but we let it go as nothing was stolen. My main complaint is with the housekeeping the rest of the hotel was very nice. And the housekeeping Managers were very nice, not their fault. On our second stay my only other complaint was when I got home I looked at my visa charges to see that I was charged an additional $85, when I called the hotel they said it was for the entire mini bar contents and also Movies, Well we rented no movies on the tv and never even opened the mini bar as we saw the price list on the out side no thanks. I was however immediatly helped and they told me without a single fuss that they would reverse the charges and they did within a week the charges were reversed. So that was good. Also I heard no noise what so ever like I have read in other reviews of thin walls... maybe we were lucky?. There was some construction going on but you have to realize these construction people may start early but that is because it can get to a sweltering 116 degrees in the direct sun by 12 noon and can you imagine being a construction worker and having to deal with that plus they make next to nothing for that. Sooo give the constuction a break it is only to make Vegas more beautiful next time you return. People who dont like the noise, bring ear plugs you are in Vegas and people love to party be prepared. Also I was lucky enough to come back for a 4 day stay at Buffalo Bills in Primm at the state line one night which was very nice compared to Whiskey Petes and Primm Valley Resort and then stayed at The Tropicana the other 3 nights over 4th of July weekend 2006. Please note Tropicana has a beautiful Pool for summer time with swim up blackjack and a huge waterfall lots of fun we go every summer to stay at the Tropicana. But that weekend I came to the Palms to go to the Pool with a friend that was staying there and also to make some bets for the Daytona 500, we went out to the pool and asked what was going on as it was packed. We