Sep 28 2005	The Palms- Almost perfect.	I stayed at the Palms from Sept 19 thru the 25th of this year.The taxi from the airport to the palms was over $20 with tip. From the Palms to the airport to leave Las vegas it was about $9 with tip. I walked up to check in with no line and was on my way up to my room in under 30 seconds. The room was on the 5th floor and had two double beds and a bathroom that was big enough for two people to get ready at once if needed. The bed was very confortable with the sheets being really soft. Mattress was a little hard but i am used to a waterbed which is why i think it felt that way. The shower had great water pressure and the water itself stayed hot the whole time. One problem in the bathroom was if you turned the cold water faucett in the sink a little to much the pipes rattled big time. The biggest problem i had was that the walls are a little to thin as you can hear doors slamming,the conversation of the room next to you and you know when they are taking a shower because you can hear the water running. My room was on the Club Rain end and you could feel the vibration of the bass if you went to bed before the club closed. I did not care as i did not go to Vegas to sleep that much. Room service was great and reloaded me every morning with towels and shower supplies.There are plenty of upscale restaurants to choose from and a food court for those like me. I was at skin every day laying out by the pool which is smaller than i thought it would be. Be warned, they are doing major construction at skin so there is no peace and quiet as they were and are tearing down the buildings to add a 33 million dollar expansion for the pool area next year. A life guard told me that Skin will be closing two months early this year so they can complete the project by next spring. The new Palms place they are building also blocks the sun for about 90 minutes every day so the pool is in complete shade during that time. Small mixed drinks were $9 with a large costing $13. Service was great and fast even when ordering food. Skin also closes at 5pm which means you have no where to go after that if you want to stay outside and get some more sun. I was at Rain on Thursday and Saturday nights and had no problem getting to the bar and getting drinks even though the club was packed. I never waited more than a minute to be waited on. Yager Bombs cost $11 if that is your drink of choice so i assume the other drinks are in that range also. They need to bring the Go Go dancers back though as they are fun to watch. Yes they pack the people in but that is the fun of people watching. I played the slots and never had to wait that long for a cocktail waitress to ask me if i wanted anything. They were very friendly and struck up conversation when they had the chance. Everybody who i talked to that worked there from the desk to security was friendly and answered any questions i had. They have a free shuttle that takes you to Caesars Palace and the fashion mall but it stops running about 6:30pm. Bus to Caesars cost $1.25, Taxi to Caesars was about $7 with tip and i walked to Caesars which took about 25-30 minutes. Checkout was no hassle but they do charge you $1 a day for line service for your phone even if you did not use it. My overall experience was very good and i can not wait to come back when all the construction is done because that pool area should be awesome.	
