Apr 4 2005	The bedding alone is worth the stay!	While I did not quite fit into the hip twenty-something demographic, I did realy enjoy my stay at the Palms:Pro's:1. Amazing bedding. I loved the pillows and the comforter. There's nothing like sinking into a comfy bed after a long day, and these are the best beds I've stayed in so far in Vegas.2. It's a small casino and I like that. The mega-resorts are overwhelming and easy to get lost in. I like the small feel.3. Despite the small feel, everything you need is here: restaurants from the standard coffee shop and buffets, to fast food to groumet. There's a movie theatre onsite. The spa is nice.4. I don't have kids, but they seem to have a drop in day-care area where you can leave your kids for five hours max. I don't know the cost, but what a great idea. If I had kids, this would be a major plus!5. Great bathroom. The vanity is great for applying make-up.6. Our room had an amazing view of the strip!7. Despite reports to the contrary, they do have good games there if you stick to video poker and look for the games that say over 100% return. But they are a casino, and most of the slots will cost you money. Most people do lose in Vegas. But the odds on the video poker and slot games are in general better than you find on the strip. Beware the table games though. 6:5 blackjack is a joke.Cons1. As others have noted, the walls are thin. I am a heavy sleeper, so not a big deal to me, but I did hear our neighbors in the morning, and I could hear everything they were saying even though they did not seem to be talking loudly.2. If you are not young and hip, you can feel out of place. I did at times. As an overweight female the place can feel intimidating. 3. The lines for the night clubs make it hard to get back to your room at night; it is a little hard to navigate.4. What's up with the 6:5 blackjack?5. The poker room allows smoking, where most of the other Vegas poker rooms are now non-smoking	
