Oct 20 2004	I Disagree ....	I stayed here in September 2004 and really liked this hotel, I dont know why everyone is so dismissive. Ok, so the reception area / casino isnt as impressive as say the Aladdin or Bellagio, but if your looking for a casino, its got all you need, ie. machines, tables, etc! The room we had was fantastic, we were only on the eighth floor, but the views were amazing. Being away from the strip meant that you could get the full scenic view from your bedroom. The bathroom was immense, with a &quot;movie star&quot; type mirror (with bulbs around it) covering a large part of the wall. The beds were VERY comfortable and the rooms always felt clean and, even though the sheets werent changed every day, they always made the bed back to how it was the night before. The pool area was lovely to just chill out and relax. The music wasnt overly loud, the pool was never over-crowded and there was always somewhere to sit / lay as the area is so large. The waiter service was a bit expensive, but there was nothing to stop you walking over to the bar to get your drinks to save on the cost. The hotel is positioned just off the strip, but there is a free bus that runs from the hotel about four times a day and drops you at four locations on the strip and also there is the local bus that stops right outside the hotel, runs every 10 mins and only cost $1.25. We had a fantastic time when we stayed at The Palms and I'd recommend for anyone to stay here ... just dont expect it to be a wild party house, its just a nice hotel to stay at.	
