Feb 16 2004	Great for the young 20-30 crowd	This was a great place to stay. We were there in the off season (early Feb), but it was still full of activity. To save some $, we packed 5 in a room, and had them wheel in a cot for $25 a night. The best part about staying here, as opposed to just going here, is you get some VIP access. It's not much, but it counts- you get front of the line or VIP line service at both Ghost Bar and Rain, as long as you are there before they fill up. Note that this can be really early, like 9:00 PM for Ghost Bar and 11:30 PM for Rain on Fri/Sat, but it beats waiting in the lines you will see if you show up later. As for the rest of the place, the rooms are nice, the $6 buffet is good on weekdays, though on weekends the $12 &quot;champagne brunch&quot; is a bit of a rip off. Also, the casino is small, so it doesn't have the impact of some of the bigger places on the strip. All-in-all, this was without a doubt a great decision- staff was friendly, even the bouncers/security. Coming from NYC, where they can be a litte bit rude and holier-than-thou, it was great to be able to ask questions and get helpful answers from the doormen. If your friends say they don't want to stay off the strip, slap 'em on the head, because you're just going to end up going here at night anyway, and it was great to just come out of the club, hit the tables for a while, and then head upstairs to bed, rather than deal with the hordes fighting for cabs outside.	
